&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Five friends &amp;mdash; Maha, Renu, Banu, Suji and Thanu travel to five different cities &amp;mdash; &amp;#39;P&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;Q&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;R&amp;#39;, &amp;#39;S&amp;#39; and &amp;#39;T&amp;#39; by five different modes of transport &amp;mdash;bus, train, aero plane, car and boat.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1)&amp;nbsp;Banu travels to &amp;#39;S&amp;#39; by car, and Renu travels to &amp;#39;Q&amp;#39; by aero plane.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2)&amp;nbsp;Suji travels by boat whereas Thanu travels by train.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As only one position is left in transport, therefore will be occupied by the mode of transport left i.e. Bus.&lt;/p&gt;

